[
  {
    "content": "**\`Pending\`**",
    "title": "RRC Framework Full Implementation",
  },
  {
    "content": "The documents herein define the parameters of the Ethena USDe Instance of the Allocation System Primitive.",
    "title": "Parameters",
  },
  {
    "content": "The documents herein define the Instance identifiers.",
    "title": "Instance Identifiers",
  },
  {
    "content": "Ethereum Mainnet",
    "title": "Network",
  },
  {
    "content": "Ethena Protocol",
    "title": "Target Protocol",
  },
  {
    "content": "USDC",
    "title": "Asset Supplied By Grove Liquidity Layer",
  },
  {
    "content": "USDe",
    "title": "Token",
  },
  {
    "content": "The documents herein define the Instance contract addresses.",
    "title": "Contract Addresses",
  },
  {
    "content": "\`0x4c9EDD5852cd905f086C759E8383e09bff1E68B3\`",
    "title": "Token Address",
  },
  {
    "content": "This parameter will be specified in a future iteration of the Grove Artifact.",
    "title": "Underlying Asset Address",
  },
  {
    "content": "\`0xe3490297a08d6fC8Da46Edb7B6142E4F461b62D3\`",
    "title": "EthenaMinter",
  },
  {
    "content": "The specific \`RateLimitID\`(s) for this conduit’s inflow and outflow will be specified in a future iteration of the Grove Artifact.",
    "title": "Rate Limit IDs",
  },
  {
    "content": "The current \`maxAmount\` and \`slope\` for this conduit’s inflow/outflow are defined in the subdocuments herein.",
    "title": "Rate Limits",
  },
  {
    "content": "The inflow rate limits are:

- \`maxAmount\`: 250,000,000
- \`slope\`: 100,000,000 per day",
    "title": "Inflow Rate Limits",
  },
  {
    "content": "The outflow rate limits are:

- \`maxAmount\`: 500,000,000
- \`slope\`: 200,000,000 per day",
    "title": "Outflow Rate Limits",
  },
  {
    "content": "The documents herein contain specific off-chain parameters for this Instance.",
    "title": "Off-chain Operational Parameters",
  },
  {
    "content": "The documents herein defines the operations performed to manage the Ethena Instance, including rate limiting, role-based access control, and cooldown functionality.",
    "title": "Instance-specific Operational Processes",
  },
  {
    "content": "The documents herein contain the addresses authorized as \`delegatedSigners\` in the \`ethenaMinter\` contract. \`delegatedSigners\` are set up and removed in the \`MainnetController\` contract by the \`Relayer\` role.",
    "title": "Delegated Signers",
  },
  {
    "content": "\`delegatedSigner\` addresses

- These addesses will be specified in a future iteration of the Spark Artifact.",
    "title": "Addresses Of Delegated Signers",
  },
  {
    "content": "The documents herein define the process for an operator to set a delegated signer to the EthenaMinter contract.",
    "title": "Set A Delegated Signer In The EthenaMinter Contract",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must ensure they are working as a \`RELAYER\`. Only the \`RELAYER\` role is allowed to \`setDelegatedSigner\`. Also, they must ensure the contract \`isActive\` i.e. can process the request.

\`\`\`
function setDelegatedSigner(address delegatedSigner)
        external
        onlyRole(RELAYER)
        isActive
\`\`\`",
    "title": "Relayer Role",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must use \`proxy.doCall()\` to forward the call to the \`ethenaMinter\` contract and call \`setDelegatedSigner\` function to set the address that will be authorized as a \`delegatedSigner\`. To call on \`ethenaMinter\` contract, the function must be encoded using \`abi.encodeCall\`.

\`\`\`
{
    proxy.doCall(
        address(ethenaMinter),
        abi.encodeCall(ethenaMinter.setDelegatedSigner, (address(delegatedSigner)))
    );
}
\`\`\`",
    "title": "Encode Function",
  },
  {
    "content": "The documents herein define the process for an operator to remove a delegated signer from the Ethena Minter contract.",
    "title": "Remove A Delegated Signer In The Ethena Minter Contract",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must ensure they are working as a \`RELAYER\`. Only the \`RELAYER\` role is allowed to \`removeDelegatedSigner\`. Also, they must ensure the contract \`isActive\` i.e. can process the request.

\`\`\`
function removeDelegatedSigner(address delegatedSigner)
        external
        onlyRole(RELAYER)
        isActive
\`\`\`",
    "title": "Relayer Role",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must use \`proxy.doCall()\` to forward the call to the \`ethenaMinter\` contract and call \`removeDelegatedSigner\` function to remove the authorization for the \`address\` to act as a \`delegatedSigner\`. To call on \`ethenaMinter\` contract, the function must be encoded using \`abi.encodeCall\`.

\`\`\`
{
    proxy.doCall(
        address(ethenaMinter),
        abi.encodeCall(ethenaMinter.removeDelegatedSigner, (address(delegatedSigner)))
    );
}
\`\`\`",
    "title": "Encode Function",
  },
  {
    "content": "The documents herein define the process for an operator to approve the minting of USDe by the EthenaMinter contract.",
    "title": "Approve Minting of USDe By Ethena Minter Contract",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must ensure they are working as a \`RELAYER\`. Only the \`RELAYER\` role is allowed to \`prepareUSDeMint\`. Also, they must ensure the contract \`isActive\` i.e. can process the request.

\`\`\`
function prepareUSDeMint(uint256 usdcAmount)
        external
        onlyRole(RELAYER)
        isActive
\`\`\`",
    "title": "Relayer Role",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must enforce a rate limit on how much USDC can be approved for minting USDe.

\`rateLimited(LIMIT_USDE_MINT, usdcAmount)\`",
    "title": "Enforce Rate Limit",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must use \`proxy.doCall()\` to send an approval call to the \`usdc\` contract, allowing the \`ethenaMinter\` contract to spend up to the specified \`amount\` of USDC. They must encode the function using \`abi.encodeCall\`.

\`\`\`
 {
    proxy.doCall(
        address(usdc),
        abi.encodeCall(usdc.approve, (address(ethenaMinter), usdcAmount))
    );
}
\`\`\`",
    "title": "Encode Function",
  },
  {
    "content": "The documents herein define the process for an operator to approve the burning of USDe by the EthenaMinter contract.",
    "title": "Approve Burning of USDe By EthenaMinter Contract",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must ensure they are working as a \`RELAYER\`. Only the \`RELAYER\` role is allowed to \`prepareUSDeBurn\`. Also, they must ensure the contract \`isActive\` i.e. can process the request.

\`\`\`
function prepareUSDeBurn(uint256 usdeAmount)
        external
        onlyRole(RELAYER)
        isActive
\`\`\`",
    "title": "Relayer Role",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must enforce a rate limit on how much USDe can be approved for burning.

\`rateLimited(LIMIT_USDE_BURN, usdeAmount)\`",
    "title": "Enforce Rate Limit",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must use \`proxy.doCall()\` to send an approval call to the \`usde\` contract, allowing the \`ethenaMinter\` contract to spend up to the specified \`amount\` of USDe. They must encode the function using \`abi.encodeCall\`.

\`\`\`
{
    proxy.doCall(
        address(usde),
        abi.encodeCall(usde.approve, (address(ethenaMinter), usdeAmount))
    );
}
\`\`\`",
    "title": "Encode Function",
  },
]
`;

exports[`allocation-system sub-doc content > Grove > Ethereum Mainnet - Ethena sUSDe 1`] = `
[
  {
    "content": "**\`Pending\`**",
    "title": "RRC Framework Full Implementation",
  },
  {
    "content": "The documents herein define the parameters of the Ethena sUSDe Instance of the Allocation System Primitive.",
    "title": "Parameters",
  },
  {
    "content": "The documents herein define the Instance identifiers.",
    "title": "Instance Identifiers",
  },
  {
    "content": "Ethereum Mainnet",
    "title": "Network",
  },
  {
    "content": "Ethena Protocol",
    "title": "Target Protocol",
  },
  {
    "content": "USDe",
    "title": "Asset Supplied By Grove Liquidity Layer",
  },
  {
    "content": "sUSDe",
    "title": "Token",
  },
  {
    "content": "The documents herein define the Instance contract addresses.",
    "title": "Contract Addresses",
  },
  {
    "content": "\`0x9D39A5DE30e57443BfF2A8307A4256c8797A3497\`",
    "title": "Token Address",
  },
  {
    "content": "\`0x4c9EDD5852cd905f086C759E8383e09bff1E68B3\`",
    "title": "Underlying Asset Address",
  },
  {
    "content": "\`0xe3490297a08d6fC8Da46Edb7B6142E4F461b62D3\`",
    "title": "EthenaMinter",
  },
  {
    "content": "The specific \`RateLimitID\`(s) for this conduit’s inflow and outflow will be specified in a future iteration of the Grove Artifact.",
    "title": "Rate Limit IDs",
  },
  {
    "content": "The current \`maxAmount\` and \`slope\` for this conduit’s inflow/outflow are defined in the subdocuments herein.",
    "title": "Rate Limits",
  },
  {
    "content": "The inflow rate limits are:

- \`maxAmount\`: 250,000,000
- \`slope\`: 100,000,000 per day",
    "title": "Inflow Rate Limits",
  },
  {
    "content": "The outflow rate limits are:

- \`maxAmount\`: unlimited
- \`slope\`: unlimited",
    "title": "Outflow Rate Limits",
  },
  {
    "content": "The documents herein contain specific off-chain parameters for this Instance.",
    "title": "Off-chain Operational Parameters",
  },
  {
    "content": "For operational processes defining the operations performed to manage the Ethena Instance, including rate limiting, role-based access control, and minting of USDe functionality see Instance-specific Operational Processes. For detailed logic specific for this instance see [A.6.1.1.2.2.6.1.3.1.4.2.3.1 - Initiate A sUSDe Cooldown Period](2e467f99-83b9-48a0-adf5-9cc5c538fb23), [A.6.1.1.2.2.6.1.3.1.4.2.3.2 - Cool Down sUSDe Shares](8f029eaf-a208-4f7c-8f00-d34b1e15ca08), [A.6.1.1.2.2.6.1.3.1.4.2.3.3 - Unstake sUSDe And Return It To ALM Proxy](bf0523c1-7c37-4073-b565-202c5497825c) and [A.6.1.1.2.2.6.1.3.1.4.2.3.4 - Emergency Procedure To Withdraw Ethena Balances](8d926497-9fe7-4189-83c8-10f649ff0b1d).",
    "title": "Instance-specific Operational Processes",
  },
  {
    "content": "The documents herein define the process for an operator to initiate a sUSDe Cooldown period.",
    "title": "Initiate A sUSDe Cooldown Period",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must ensure they are working as a \`RELAYER\`. Only the \`RELAYER\` role is allowed to \`cooldownAssetsSUSDe\`. Also, they must ensure the contract \`isActive\` i.e. can process the request.

\`\`\`
function cooldownAssetsSUSDe(uint256 usdeAmount)
        external
        onlyRole(RELAYER)
        isActive
\`\`\`",
    "title": "Relayer Role",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must enforce a rate limit on how much sUSDe can be cooled down.

\`rateLimited(LIMIT_SUSDE_COOLDOWN, usdeAmount)\`",
    "title": "Enforce Rate Limit",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must use \`proxy.doCall()\` to make a call to the \`susde\` contract, invoking the \`cooldownAssets\` function with the specified amount of sUSDe. They must encode the function using \`abi.encodeCall\`.

\`\`\`
{
    proxy.doCall(
        address(susde),
        abi.encodeCall(susde.cooldownAssets, (usdeAmount))
    );
}
\`\`\`",
    "title": "Encode Function",
  },
  {
    "content": "The documents herein define the process for an operator to cool down sUSDe shares.",
    "title": "Cool Down sUSDe Shares",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must ensure they are working as a \`RELAYER\`. Only the \`RELAYER\` role is allowed to \`cooldownSharesSUSDe\`. Also, they must ensure the contract \`isActive\` i.e. can process the request.

\`\`\`
function cooldownSharesSUSDe(uint256 susdeAmount)
        external
        onlyRole(RELAYER)
        isActive
\`\`\`",
    "title": "Relayer Role",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must use \`proxy.doCall()\` to make a call to the \`susde\` contract, initiating the \`cooldown\` on the specified amount of sUSDe shares. They must encode the function using \`abi.encodeCall\`.",
    "title": "Encode Function",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must decode the result returned by the \`cooldownShares\` function into a \`uint256\` value, representing the amount of shares that were actually cooled down (\`cooldownAmount\`).

\`\`\`
{
    cooldownAmount = abi.decode(
        proxy.doCall(
            address(susde),
            abi.encodeCall(susde.cooldownShares, (susdeAmount))
        ),
        (uint256)
    );
\`\`\`",
    "title": "Decode For Underlying Shares",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must decrease the \`RateLimit\`, effectively reducing the available \`cooldown\` limit, based on the \`cooldownAmount\`.

\`\`\`
rateLimits.triggerRateLimitDecrease(LIMIT_SUSDE_COOLDOWN, cooldownAmount);
}
\`\`\`",
    "title": "Decrease RateLimit",
  },
  {
    "content": "The documents herein define the process for an operator to unstake sUSDe and return it to the ALM Proxy.",
    "title": "Unstake sUSDe And Return It To ALM Proxy",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must ensure they are working as a \`RELAYER\`. Only the \`RELAYER\` role is allowed to \`unstakeSUSDe\`. Also, they must ensure the contract \`isActive\` i.e. can process the request.

\`\`\`
function unstakeSUSDe()
        external
        onlyRole(RELAYER)
        isActive
\`\`\`",
    "title": "Relayer Role",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must use \`proxy.doCall()\` to make a call to the \`susde\` contract to invoke the \`unstake\` function, which unstakes sUSDe and sends the resulting tokens back to the \`proxy\` address (i.e. ALM Proxy). They must encode the function using \`abi.encodeCall\`.

\`\`\`
{
    proxy.doCall(
        address(susde),
        abi.encodeCall(susde.unstake, (address(proxy)))
    );
}
\`\`\`",
    "title": "Encode Function",
  },
  {
    "content": "In order to withdraw all Ethena balances, the operator must execute the following actions:",
    "title": "Emergency Procedure To Withdraw Ethena Balances",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must start the cooldown for sUSDe using the following action:

\`\`\`
mainnetController.cooldownSharesSUSDe(susde.balanceOf(address(proxy))
\`\`\`
For more detailed instructions on the code to execute this, see [A.6.1.1.2.2.6.1.3.1.4.2.3.2 - Cool Down sUSDe Shares](8f029eaf-a208-4f7c-8f00-d34b1e15ca08).",
    "title": "sUSDe Cooldown Action",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must unstake sUSDe using the following action:

\`\`\`
mainnetController.unstakeSUSDe()
\`\`\`
For more detailed instructions on the code to execute this, see [A.6.1.1.2.2.6.1.3.1.4.2.3.3 - Unstake sUSDe And Return It To ALM Proxy](bf0523c1-7c37-4073-b565-202c5497825c).",
    "title": "sUSDe Unstake Action",
  },
]
`;

