exports[`allocation-system sub-doc content > Spark > Ethereum Mainnet - Aave Prime USDS 1`] = `
[
  {
    "content": "**\`Covered\`**",
    "title": "RRC Framework Full Implementation",
  },
  {
    "content": "The documents herein define the parameters of the Aave Prime USDS Instance of the Allocation System Primitive.",
    "title": "Parameters",
  },
  {
    "content": "The documents herein define the Instance identifiers",
    "title": "Instance Identifiers",
  },
  {
    "content": "Ethereum Mainnet",
    "title": "Network",
  },
  {
    "content": "Aave Prime",
    "title": "Target Protocol",
  },
  {
    "content": "USDS",
    "title": "Asset Supplied By Spark Liquidity Layer",
  },
  {
    "content": "aEthLidoUSDS",
    "title": "Token",
  },
  {
    "content": "The documents herein define the Instance contract addresses.",
    "title": "Contract Addresses",
  },
  {
    "content": "\`0x09AA30b182488f769a9824F15E6Ce58591Da4781\`",
    "title": "Token Address",
  },
  {
    "content": "\`0xdC035D45d973E3EC169d2276DDab16f1e407384F\`",
    "title": "Underlying Asset Address",
  },
  {
    "content": "This parameter will be specified in a future iteration of the Spark Artifact.",
    "title": "Pool",
  },
  {
    "content": "The specific \`RateLimitID\`(s) for this conduit’s inflow and outflow will be specified in a future iteration of the Spark Artifact.",
    "title": "Rate Limit IDs",
  },
  {
    "content": "The current \`maxAmount\` and \`slope\` for this conduit’s inflow/outflow are defined in the subdocuments herein.",
    "title": "Rate Limits",
  },
  {
    "content": "The inflow rate limits are:

- \`maxAmount\`: 0
- \`slope\`: 50,000,000 USDS per day",
    "title": "Inflow Rate Limits",
  },
  {
    "content": "The outflow rate limits are:

- \`maxAmount\`: 0
- \`slope\`: Unlimited",
    "title": "Outflow Rate Limits",
  },
  {
    "content": "The documents herein contain specific off-chain parameters for this Instance.",
    "title": "Off-chain Operational Parameters",
  },
  {
    "content": "The documents herein contain operational procedures or monitoring requirements unique to this Instance that deviate from or otherwise supplement the general Spark Liquidity Layer processes. For the general operational procedures applicable to all Aave-type instances. See [A.6.1.1.1.2.6.1.2.2.1.2.1.2.3 - Aave Functions](9922dcf0-4562-445b-9a46-712f677cce64) and [A.6.1.1.1.2.6.1.2.2.3.2.3 - Aave AToken Withdrawal Action](2560adbb-4a5c-4c95-86cb-04647bb33836).",
    "title": "Instance-specific Operational Processes",
  },
  {
    "content": "The documents herein define the steps to deposit assets from the ALM Proxy to the Aave pool to receive yield-bearing ATokens.",
    "title": "Process Definition For Depositing",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must ensure they are working as a \`RELAYER\`. Only the \`RELAYER\` role is allowed to \`depositAave\`. Also, they must ensure the contract \`isActive\` i.e. can process the request.

\`\`\`
function depositAave(address aToken, uint256 amount)
external
onlyRole(RELAYER)
isActive
\`\`\`",
    "title": "Relayer Role",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must ensure ALM Proxy holds enough of the underlying asset to cover the instructed \`deposit\` amount.",
    "title": "Check ALM Proxy",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must ensure the \`deposit\` amount is allowed within the \`RateLimits\`.

        \`rateLimited(
RateLimitHelpers.makeAssetKey(LIMIT_AAVE_DEPOSIT, aToken),
amount
)\`",
    "title": "Check RateLimits",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must initialize the \`underlying\` variable as an ERC-20 token interface.",
    "title": "Initialize ERC-20 Token Interface",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must initialize the interface for the \`address of the underlying asset\` retrieved from the \`aToken\` contract (the contract that represents the deposited assets in Aave). The \`IERC20\` interface allows interaction with ERC-20 tokens, including performing actions like transferring, approving, and checking balances.

\`\`\`
 {
IERC20    underlying = IERC20(IATokenWithPool(aToken).UNDERLYING_ASSET_ADDRESS());
\`\`\`",
    "title": "Initialize Interface For Address",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must initialize the \`pool\` variable as an interface for the Aave pool.",
    "title": "Initialize Pool Variable",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must retrieve the Aave pool contract address associated with the given \`aToken\`. This address represents the Aave lending pool where the assets are deposited. \`IAavePool\` interface allows interaction with the Aave pool's functions (like \`supply\`).

\`    IAavePool pool       = IAavePool(IATokenWithPool(aToken).POOL());\`",
    "title": "Retrieve Aave Address",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must call the \`approve\` function to update the allowance of the \`underlying\` asset contract.",
    "title": "Call Approve Function",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must encode the \`approve\` function call, using \`abi.encodeCall\` allowing the Aave \`pool\` address to spend up to \`amount\` of the \`underlying\` token from the ALM Proxy’s balance.",
    "title": "Encode Function Call",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must send the encoded call using \`proxy.doCall()\` specifying the \`address\` of the \`asset\` contract they want to deposit into.

       \`// Approve underlying to Aave pool from the proxy (assumes the proxy has enough underlying).
proxy.doCall(
address(underlying),
abi.encodeCall(underlying.approve, (address(pool), amount))
);\`",
    "title": "Send Encoded Call",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must call the \`deposit\` function to transfer the \`underlying\` asset to the Aave lending pool and receive the \`aTokens\`.",
    "title": "Call Deposit Function",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must encode the \`deposit\` function call, using \`abi.encodeCall\` with the address of the \`underlying\` token, the \`amount\` of the underlying asset to \`deposit\` and the \`address(proxy)\` that will receive the resulting \`aTokens\` (i.e. ALM Proxy).",
    "title": "Encode Function Call",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must send the encoded call using \`proxy.doCall()\` to the \`supply\` function on Aave (\`pool\`).

        \`// Deposit underlying into Aave pool, proxy receives aTokens
proxy.doCall(
address(pool),
abi.encodeCall(pool.supply, (address(underlying), amount, address(proxy), 0))
);
}\`",
    "title": "Send Encoded Call",
  },
  {
    "content": "The documents herein define the steps for an operator to withdraw a yield-earning balance from the Aave AToken vaults to the ALM Proxy.",
    "title": "Process Definition For Withdrawing",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must ensure they are working as a \`RELAYER\`. Only the \`RELAYER\` role is allowed to \`withdrawAave\` tokens. Also, they ensure the contract \`isActive\` i.e. can process the request.

\`\`\`
function withdrawAave(address aToken, uint256 amount)
external
onlyRole(RELAYER)
isActive
\`\`\`",
    "title": "Relayer Role",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must ensure the ALM Proxy holds sufficient \`aTokens\` to cover the instructed \`withdraw\` amount.",
    "title": "Check ALM Proxy",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must ensure the \`withdraw\` amount is allowed within the \`RateLimits\`.

\`\`\`
// Check withdrawal limits.
rateLimited(
RateLimitHelpers.makeAssetKey(LIMIT_AAVE_WITHDRAW, aToken),
amount
)
\`\`\`",
    "title": "Check RateLimits",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must initialize the \`pool\` variable as an interface for the Aave pool.",
    "title": "Initialize Pool Variable",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must retrieve the Aave pool contract address associated with the given \`aToken\`. This address represents the Aave lending pool from which the assets are withdrawn.

    \`IAavePool pool       = IAavePool(IATokenWithPool(aToken).POOL());\`",
    "title": "Retrieve Aave Address",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must call the \`withdraw\` function to withdraw a required amount of \`underlying\` asset from Aave \`pool\` address and receive the corresponding \`aTokens\`.",
    "title": "Call Withdraw Function",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must encode the \`withdraw\` function using \`abi.encodeCall\` with the \`underlying asset address\` from the \`aToken\` contract, specifying which token is being withdrawn, the \`amount\` of the underlying asset to \`withdraw\`, and the \`address(proxy)\` of the recipient of the withdrawn assets (i.e. ALM Proxy).",
    "title": "Encode Function Call",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must send the encoded call using \`proxy.doCall()\` to the \`withdraw\` function of the Aave \`pool\` contract.",
    "title": "Send Encoded Call",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must decode the raw bytes data returned from the \`doCall()\` function into \`uint256\` value, representing the amount of underlying assets that were successfully withdrawn from the Aave pool (\`amountWithdrawn\`).

       \` // Withdraw underlying from Aave pool, decode resulting amount withdrawn.
// Assumes proxy has adequate aTokens.
amountWithdrawn = abi.decode(
proxy.doCall(
address(pool),
abi.encodeCall(
pool.withdraw,
(IATokenWithPool(aToken).UNDERLYING_ASSET_ADDRESS(), amount, address(proxy))
)
),
(uint256)
);\`",
    "title": "Decode For Underlying Assets",
  },
  {
    "content": "The operator must decrease the \`RateLimit\` based on the assets redeemed.

\`\`\`
rateLimits.triggerRateLimitDecrease(
            RateLimitHelpers.makeAssetKey(LIMIT_AAVE_WITHDRAW, aToken),
            amountWithdrawn
        );
    }
\`\`\`",
    "title": "Decrease RateLimit",
  },
]
`;

